import numpy as np

import skfuzzy as fuzz
from skfuzzy import control as ctrl
from sklearn.mixture import GaussianMixture
from sklearn.cluster import SpectralClustering
import time
from sklearn.metrics import silhouette_score
import folium
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

class clusterplot:
    def __init__(self,csv_file,weights):
        self.csv_file=pd.read_csv(csv_file)
        self.weights=weights
        
    def data_visualisation_preprocessing(self):
        print("Showing Top 5 values of the Selected Data Set")
        self.head=self.csv_file.head()
        self.desired_value = self.csv_file[self.csv_file['weight'] > self.weights]
#         self.df11=self.df[['latitude1','longitude1','sector_id1']]
        self.df=self.desired_value.iloc[:,[5,6]].values
    
        return self.df  
            
    def Gaussian_clustering_prediction(self,n_component):
        
        self.labels=[]
        self.score=[]
        st = time.time()
        self.gmm = GaussianMixture(n_components=n_component)
        self.gmm_model=self.gmm.fit(self.df)
        self.labels=self.gmm.predict(self.df)
        et=time.time()
        return print('Time taken to form the Gaussian Cluster is ',et-st),self.labels
        
    def Spectural_clustering_prediction(self,number_of_cluster):
        self.labels2=[]
        self.score2=[]
        st = time.time()
        sc = SpectralClustering(n_clusters=number_of_cluster, affinity='nearest_neighbors', random_state=0)
        sc_clustering = sc.fit(self.df)
        self.labels2=(sc_clustering.labels_)
        et=time.time()
        
        return print("The time taken to form the Spectural Clustering is ",et-st),self.labels2

            
    def fuzzy_c_mean_clustering_prediction(self,n_clusters):
        self.labels3=[]
        self.score3=[]
        st = time.time()
        cntr, u, u0, d, jm, p, fpc = fuzz.cluster.cmeans(self.df.T, n_clusters, 2, error=0.005, maxiter=1000, init=None)
        cluster_membership=np.argmax(u,axis=0)
        self.labels3=cluster_membership
        st = time.time()
        return print("The time taken to form the fuzzy c mean cluster is ",et-st), self.labels3
        
    
    
    def preparting_presentation(self,model_selected,n_cluster):
        self.df11=self.desired_value[['latitude1','longitude1','sector_id1']]
        self.df0=self.desired_value[['latitude0','longitude0','sector_id0']]
        self.desired_value["first"] = self.desired_value[["latitude0","longitude0"]].apply(tuple, axis=1)
        self.desired_value["second"] = self.desired_value[["latitude1","longitude1"]].apply(tuple, axis=1)
        if model_selected=='Gaussian Cluster':
             self.desired_value['classification']=self.Gaussian_clustering_prediction(n_cluster)[1]
        elif model_selected=='spectural_cluster':
            self.desired_value['classification']=self.Spectural_clustering_prediction(n_cluster)[1]
        else:
            self.desired_value['classification']=self.fuzzy_c_mean_clustering_prediction(n_cluster)[1] 
            
        rating=[]
        for row in self.desired_value['classification']:
            if row == 1 :
                rating.append('red')
            elif row == 2:
                rating.append('green')
            elif row == 3:
                rating.append('blue')
            elif row ==4:
                rating.append('purple')
            elif row == 5:
                rating.append('orange')
            elif row == 6:
                rating.append('darkred')
            elif row == 7:
                rating.append('lightred')
            elif row == 8:
                rating.append('beige')
            elif row == 9:
                rating.append('darkblue')
            elif row == 10:
                rating.append('darkgreen')
            elif row == 11:
                rating.append('cadetblue')
            elif row == 12:
                rating.append('darkpurple')
            elif row == 13:
                rating.append('white')
            elif row == 14:
                rating.append('lightblue')
            elif row == 15:
                rating.append('lightgreen')
            elif row == 16:
                rating.append('gray')
            elif row == 17:
                rating.append('black')
            elif row == 18:
                rating.append('lightgray')
            elif row == 19:
                rating.append('purple')
            elif row == 20:
                rating.append('orange')
            elif row == 21:
                rating.append('darkred')
            elif row == 22:
                rating.append('darkgreen')
            elif row == 23:
                rating.append('darkpurple')
            elif row == 24:
                rating.append('beige')
            elif row == 25:
                rating.append('lightgreen')
            elif row == 26:
                rating.append('green')
            elif row == 27:
                rating.append('white')
            elif row == 28:
                rating.append('gray')
            elif row == 29:
                rating.append('black')
            else: 
                
                rating.append('blue')
        self.desired_value['colour']=rating
        self.m = folium.Map(location=[8.856070, 76.937560])
        
        for i in range(len(self.df0)):
            folium.Marker(
                location=[self.df0.iloc[i, 0], self.df0.iloc[i, 1]],
                popup=self.df0.iloc[i, 2],
                icon=folium.Icon(color=self.desired_value.iloc[i,10]),).add_to(self.m)
            
        for i in range(len(self.df11)):
            folium.Marker(
                location=[self.df11.iloc[i, 0],self.df11.iloc[i, 1]],
                popup=self.df11.iloc[i, 2],
                icon=folium.Icon(color=self.desired_value.iloc[i,10]),).add_to(self.m)
            
        return self.m
    
    def csv_generator(self,n_cluster):
        self.desired_value['Gaussian']=self.Gaussian_clustering_prediction(n_cluster)
        self.desired_value['Spectural_Clustering']=self.Spectural_clustering_prediction(n_cluster)
        self.desired_value['Fuzzy_C_mean']=self.fuzzy_c_mean_clustering_prediction(n_cluster)
        
        return self.desired_value.to_csv('output.csv')
    
    
    def comparison(self,n_cluster):
        
        ###Spectural Clustering Part
        self.values5=[]
        for i in range(2,n_cluster):
            sc = SpectralClustering(n_clusters=i, affinity='nearest_neighbors', random_state=0)
            sc_clustering = sc.fit(self.df)
            self.values5.append(sc_clustering.labels_)
            
        defends3=[]
        for i in range(2,n_cluster-3):
            defends3.append(silhouette_score(self.df, self.values5[i]))
            
        w2=range(2,n_cluster-3)
        
        
        #### Gaussian Mixture Part
        self.values6=[]
        for i in range(2,n_cluster):
            self.gmm = GaussianMixture(n_components=i)
            self.gmm_model=self.gmm.fit(self.df)
            self.values6.append(self.gmm.predict(self.df))
            
        defends4=[]
        for i in range(2,n_cluster-3):
            defends4.append(silhouette_score(self.df, self.values6[i]))
        w3=range(2,n_cluster-3)
        
            
        
            
         ####Fuzz K mean cluster   
        self.values7=[]
        for i in range(2,n_cluster):
            cntr, u, u0, d, jm, p, fpc = fuzz.cluster.cmeans(self.df.T, i, 2, error=0.005, maxiter=1000, init=None)
            cluster_membership=np.argmax(u,axis=0)
            self.values7.append(cluster_membership)
            
        defends5=[]
        for i in range(2,n_cluster-3):
            defends5.append(silhouette_score(self.df, self.values7[i]))
            
        w4=range(2,n_cluster-3)
        
        figure, axis = plt.subplots(2, 2)
        axis[0, 0].plot(w2, defends3)
        axis[0, 0].set_title("Spectural Clustering")
  

        axis[0, 1].plot(w3, defends4)
        axis[0, 1].set_title("Gaussian Clustering")
  

        axis[1, 0].plot(w4, defends5)
        axis[1, 0].set_title("Fuzzy C mean ")
        
        plt.show()

class clusterplot2:
    def __init__(self,csv_file,weights):
        self.csv_file=pd.read_csv(csv_file)
        self.weights=weights
        
    def data_visualisation_preprocessing(self):
        print("Showing Top 5 values of the Selected Data Set")
        self.head=self.csv_file.head()
        self.desired_value = self.csv_file[self.csv_file['weight'] > self.weights]
        self.df=self.desired_value.iloc[:,[5,6]].values
        return self.df
            
    def Gaussian_clustering_prediction(self,n_component):
        
        self.labels=[]
        self.score=[]
        st = time.time()
        self.gmm = GaussianMixture(n_components=n_component)
        self.gmm_model=self.gmm.fit(self.df)
        self.labels=self.gmm.predict(self.df)
        et=time.time()
        return print('Time taken to form the Gaussian Cluster is ',et-st),self.labels
        
    def Spectural_clustering_prediction(self,number_of_cluster):
        self.labels2=[]
        self.score2=[]
        st = time.time()
        sc = SpectralClustering(n_clusters=number_of_cluster, affinity='nearest_neighbors', random_state=0)
        sc_clustering = sc.fit(self.df)
        self.labels2=(sc_clustering.labels_)
        et=time.time()
        
        return print("The time taken to form the Spectural Clustering is ",et-st),self.labels2

            
    def fuzzy_c_mean_clustering_prediction(self,n_clusters):
        self.labels3=[]
        self.score3=[]
        st = time.time()
        cntr, u, u0, d, jm, p, fpc = fuzz.cluster.cmeans(self.df.T, n_clusters, 2, error=0.005, maxiter=1000, init=None)
        cluster_membership=np.argmax(u,axis=0)
        self.labels3=cluster_membership
        et = time.time()
        return print("The time taken to form the fuzzy c mean cluster is ",et-st), self.labels3
        
    
    
    def preparting_presentation(self,model_selected,n_cluster):
        self.df11=self.desired_value[['latitude1','longitude1','sector_id1']]
        self.df0=self.desired_value[['latitude0','longitude0','sector_id0']]
        self.desired_value["first"] = self.desired_value[["latitude0","longitude0"]].apply(tuple, axis=1)
        self.desired_value["second"] = self.desired_value[["latitude1","longitude1"]].apply(tuple, axis=1)
        if model_selected=='Gaussian Cluster':
             self.desired_value['classification']=self.Gaussian_clustering_prediction(n_cluster)[1]
        elif model_selected=='spectural_cluster':
            self.desired_value['classification']=self.Spectural_clustering_prediction(n_cluster)[1]
        elif model_selected=='fuzzy_c_mean' :
            self.desired_value['classification']=self.fuzzy_c_mean_clustering_prediction(n_cluster)[1] 
            
        rating=[]
        colours_store=['lightred','red','darkred','lightgreen','green','darkgreen','lightblue','blue','darkblue','purple','darkpurple','orange','grey','lightgrey','beige','black','white']
        
        div=max(self.desired_value['classification'])//17 +2
        value_color=np.repeat(colours_store,div)
        for row in self.desired_value['classification']:
            
            
            for i in range(max(self.desired_value['classification'])+6):
                if row==i:
                    rating.append(value_color[i])
                
           
        
        self.desired_value['colour']=rating
        self.m = folium.Map(location=[self.csv_file['latitude1'][1], self.csv_file['longitude1'][1]])
        
        for i in range(len(self.df0)):
            folium.Marker(
                location=[self.df0.iloc[i, 0], self.df0.iloc[i, 1]],
                popup=self.df0.iloc[i, 2],
                icon=folium.Icon(color=self.desired_value.iloc[i,10]),).add_to(self.m)
            
        for i in range(len(self.df11)):
            folium.Marker(
                location=[self.df11.iloc[i, 0],self.df11.iloc[i, 1]],
                popup=self.df11.iloc[i, 2],
                icon=folium.Icon(color=self.desired_value.iloc[i,10]),).add_to(self.m)
            
        return self.m
    
    def csv_generator(self,n_cluster):
        self.desired_value['Gaussian']=self.Gaussian_clustering_prediction(n_cluster)[1]
        self.desired_value['Spectural_Clustering']=self.Spectural_clustering_prediction(n_cluster)[1]
        self.desired_value['Fuzzy_C_mean']=self.fuzzy_c_mean_clustering_prediction(n_cluster)[1]
        
        return self.desired_value.to_csv('/Users/harshraj/Desktop/CV_EXAM/cluster_file_punalur.csv')

#Stream Lit App:import streamlit as st
from clusterplot2 import clusterplot2

def main():
    st.title("Cluster CSV Data and Display on Map")
    st.set_option('deprecation.showfileUploaderEncoding', False)
    
    # Upload CSV file
    uploaded_file = st.file_uploader("Choose a CSV file")
    
    if uploaded_file is not None:
        weights = st.slider("Choose a weight", min_value=0, max_value=100, step=5, value=50)
        n_component = st.slider("Choose number of Gaussian components", min_value=2, max_value=10, step=1, value=3)
        n_clusters = st.slider("Choose number of clusters for Spectural Clustering and Fuzzy C Mean", min_value=2, max_value=10, step=1, value=3)
        model_selected = st.selectbox("Select a model", ["Gaussian Cluster", "spectural_cluster", "fuzzy_c_mean"])
        cluster_button = st.button("Cluster Data")
        
        # Cluster data and display on map
        if cluster_button:
            data = clusterplot2(uploaded_file, weights)
            data.data_visualisation_preprocessing()
            data.preparting_presentation(model_selected, n_clusters)
            st.write(data.m)
            csv_button = st.button("Generate CSV file with Clustering Results")
            
            # Generate CSV file with clustering results
            if csv_button:
                data.csv_generator(n_clusters)
                st.success("CSV file with clustering results generated successfully!")

if __name__ == "__main__":
    main()
